    "en": "When considered from the point of view of the circuit protected by a fuse, the value of the Joule-integral over the operating time of the fuse is referred to a specific energy, i.e. the energy released as heat in 1 ohm of circuit resistance."
  },
  "remark": "The value is given for the selection of fuses.",
